laboratory_examinations.findings: The gallbladder is distended with equivocal wall edema. There is cholelithiasis and small amount of gallbladder sludge. There is a 1.8 cm gallbladder neck stone which was not movable on realtime scanning and on decubitus positioning, suggesting impaction. The CBD measures 1.3 mm. There is no pericholecystic fluid with the gallbladder wall measuring 2 mm. Sonographic Murphy's sign was present.
